    "The fundamental knowledge framework of a research field comprises three components: Conceptual structure: Central themes and trends in the literature of a specific research area.",
    "Intellectual structure: The impact of an author's work within the scientific community.",
    "Social structure: Interactions among authors, institutions, and countries.",
    "Initially, the conceptual structure is examined statistically using thematic mapping [18], and keyword co-occurrence networks [19].",
    "Subsequently, the intellectual knowledge structure is evaluated through co-citation network analysis."
